<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 3:17PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...SNOW EXPANDING COVERAGE AND INCREASING INTENSITY OVER SOUTHEAST
MICHIGAN LATE THIS AFTERNOON...
WEATHER...
* Snow expands into southeast Michigan and increases intensity
during late afternoon and continues into this evening.
* Accumulation up to 1 inch is expected between 4 and 8 PM,
although up to 2 inches is likely south of I-94.
IMPACTS...
* Hazardous driving conditions develop due to low visibility and
slush or snow covered roads. Slower speed and extra travel time
will be required through the evening commute.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
